05218nam a22007695i 9780271090269DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20212021pau    fo  d z      eng d  a97802710902697 a10.1515/97802710902692doi  a(DE-B1597)589077  a(OCoLC)1266228435  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  apaucUS-PA 4aZ103.4.H86bL3613 2021eb 7aHIS0370202bisacsh04a652/.8094392231 aLáng, Benedek, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Rohonc Code :bTracing a Historical Riddle /cBenedek Láng. 1aUniversity Park, PA : bPenn State University Press, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (176 p.) :b24 illustrations  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIllustrations -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- tChapter 1 The Treasure-Hunting Bookdealer -- tChapter 2 Codebreaking Attempts -- tChapter 3 The Quest Begins -- tChapter 4 The Jesus Code -- tChapter 5 Writing in Ciphers and Codes -- tChapter 6 Decryption -- tChapter 7 Shorthand Systems -- tChapter 8 Artificial Languages and Codes -- tChapter 9 Methods of Codebreaking -- tCoda -- tAppendix -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFirst discovered in a Hungarian library in 1838, the Rohonc Codex keeps privileged company with some of the most famous unsolved writing systems in the world, notably the Voynich manuscript, the Phaistos Disk, and Linear A. Written entirely in cipher, this 400-year-old, 450-page-long, richly illustrated manuscript initially gained considerable attention but was later dismissed as an apparent forgery. No serious scholar would study it again until the turn of the twenty-first century. This engaging narrative follows historian Benedek Láng’s search to uncover the truth about this thoroughly mysterious book that has puzzled dozens of codebreakers. Láng surveys the fascinating theories associated with the Codex and discusses possible interpretations of the manuscript as a biblical commentary, an apocryphal gospel, or a secret book written for and by a sect. He provides an overview of the secret writing systems known in early modern times and an account of the numerous efforts to create an artificial language or to find a long-lost perfect tongue—endeavors that were especially popular at the time the Codex was made. Lastly, he tests several codebreaking methods in order to decipher the Codex, finally pointing to a possible solution to the enigma of its content and language system.Engagingly written, academically grounded, and thoroughly compelling, The Rohonc Code will appeal to historians, scholars, and lay readers interested in mysteries, codes, and ciphers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCiphers. 0aCryptographyzHungary. 7aHISTORY / Renaissance.2bisacsh1 aKirály, Teodóra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLáng, Benedek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalmer, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074510840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978027109026940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271090269423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271090